00:11:11.680 --> 00:11:14.760
 So this is how you make a Gravatar.

00:11:14.760 --> 00:11:20.080
 You take the user's email, you strip it, throw away any white space, you convert it to lower

00:11:20.080 --> 00:11:27.360
 case, you encode it in UTF-8, and then you use the MD5, which is a hashing function,

00:11:27.360 --> 00:11:37.800
 and make a hex digest, and that hex digest, this is an MD5, this long ugly string 2D0A2F51,

00:11:37.800 --> 00:11:43.400
 that is a one-way hash of the email address.

00:11:43.400 --> 00:11:50.620
 And if you go put that in to a thing, then if you know it, so that you can't figure out

00:11:50.620 --> 00:11:56.200
